recordings.loc: Burrillville, Providence County, Rhode Island
recordings.rmk: Canon EOS Rebel T3i built-in mic. Habitat: Successional habitat, recently logged mixed deciduous forest. Heath and blackberry make up the undergrowth. Bird called from Eastern white pine, about 20 feet up. Behavior: Calling to a nearby male. Female-type plumage. Conditions: Sunny, 80 degrees F, strong wind which was filtered out of recording to an extent. Typical "squeaky basketball shoe" call, which was what first alerted me to the bird's presence.
